The paper discusses the use of blockchain-based decentralized storage networks (DSNs) and coding solutions for wireless sensor networks (WSNs). This suggests that the paper may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses data protection and privacy, which may indicate that it belongs to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also proposes a joint coding scheme, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of wireless sensor networks may also indicate that it belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the topology of the network, which may suggest that it belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
